The build failed due to a dependency resolution exception. The error message indicates that Maven was unable to collect dependencies for the project, specifically the `co.aikar:fastutil-lite:jar:1.0` artifact. This is because the repository `http://ci.emc.gs/nexus/content/groups/aikar/` is blocked.

To resolve this issue, we need to unblock the repository or find an alternative repository that contains the required artifact. Let me try to unblock the repository by adding the following configuration to the `settings.xml` file:

<function=str_replace_editor>
<parameter=command>create</parameter>
<parameter=path>/workspace/Nukkit/settings.xml</parameter>
<parameter=file_text>
&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?&gt;
&lt;settings xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/SETTINGS/1.0.0"
          xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
          xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/SETTINGS/1.0.0
                              http://maven.apache.org/xsd/settings-1.0.0.xsd"&gt;
    &lt;mirrors&gt;
        &lt;mirror&gt;
            &lt;id&gt;aikar&lt;/id&gt;
            &lt;name&gt;aikar&lt;/name&gt;
            &lt;url&gt;http://ci.emc.gs/nexus/content/groups/aikar/&lt;/url&gt;
            &lt;mirrorOf&gt;aikar&lt;/mirrorOf&gt;
        &lt;/mirror&gt;
    &lt;/mirrors&gt;
&lt;/settings&gt;
</parameter>
</function>

It seems that the issue is still not resolved. The error message indicates that the repository `http://ci.emc.gs/nexus/content/groups/aikar/` is still blocked.

Let me try to add the repository to the `pom.xml` file:

<function=str_replace_editor>
<parameter=command>str_replace</parameter>
<parameter=path>/workspace/Nukkit/pom.xml</parameter>
<parameter=old_str>&lt;/repositories&gt;</parameter>
<parameter=new_str>
&lt;repository&gt;
    &lt;id&gt;aikar&lt;/id&gt;
    &lt;name&gt;aikar&lt;/name&gt;
    &lt;url&gt;http://ci.emc.gs/nexus/content/groups/aikar/&lt;/url&gt;
&lt;/repository&gt;
&lt;/repositories&gt;
</parameter>
</function>

It seems that the `pom.xml` file does not contain the string `&lt;/repositories&gt;`. This means that the file does not have a `repositories` section.

Let me try to add the `repositories` section to the `pom.xml` file:

